imgAlt: ['"Human parking spots" are marked at Mission Dolores Park seen during lunch time on Thursday, May 21, 2020, in San Francisco, Calif. San Francisco Recreation & Parks Department painted social-distance guidance circles on the parks lawn.', 'U.S. Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi speaking at a Capitol Hill press conference accused Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell of obstructionism regarding the relief bill.', 'A couple sunbathe on Cowell Beach in Santa Cruz in April. Warm Memorial Day weekend weather will test the Bay Area’s shelter-in-place resolve.', 'Commuters prepare to board a westbound Capitol Corridor train at the Amtrak station in Berkeley in 2018. Additional trains will be added to its schedule starting June 1.', 'People chat and embrace outside The Stud Bar in San Francisco in 2016. The 54-year old bar will close its current location at Harrison and Ninth Streets and look for a new location.', 'Isaac Conde (left), 14, and Joshua Conde, 16, walk toward Thurgood Marshall Academic High in San Francisco. The district superintendent says school will be back in session in some form on Aug. 17.', 'Workers clean Krymsky Bridge in Moscow, hich has been hit hard by the coronavirus.', 'Redwoods at the Henry Cowell Redwood State Park in Felton is seen in 2015. California State Parks began reopening some parking lots Tuesday after they were closed to discourage crowds during shelter-in-place orders.', 'Pedestrians walk through an empty Financial District in March in San Francisco. The city’s Chief Economist Ted Egan said on Tuesday, May 19, 2020, that full employment in the city could take two to three years.', 'Communities As One co-founder Josephine Zhao shops for groceries for a senior citizen on Tuesday, May 19, 2020. Asian Americans account for half of the city’s COVID-19 deaths.', 'Parking is restricted on Lakeshore Avenue and the other roads surrounding Lake Merritt in Oakland, Calif. on Saturday, May 16, 2020. Mayor Libby Schaaf said during a Tuesday  interview with ABC7 New s that new restrictions implemented last weekend at Lake Merritt worked to prevent crowds “did have the desired effect.”']
